This application will automatically detect whether the IIO devices is created.  If IIO device is not created, it will print 
a warning and exit. Otherewise, it will execute depending on the parameters it is given.

Usage:
-h: print this help
-d x: duration,  unit in seconds. default: 10 seconds
-s x: number of samples. default: 40 samples
-f x: sampling frequency. Default: 5 Hz
-l string: output logging file name. Default: /usr/chirp.csv

If this application is issued without any parameter, it will be executed with default parameters.

